<!-- Button trigger modal -->
<a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModalhelp" style="cursor:pointer">
  <img src="/images/help.png">
</a>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="myModalhelp" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel">
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Help! How to use GroupUp!?</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">

          <div align="center" class="top_logo">
            <h1><b>Help</b></h1>
            <h3>
              This is the general user guide to help our Groupers!
            </h3> 
          </div>

        <!-- ........................................................................... -->



        <!-- ...........................................................................
            ............................................................................
            Main part : Contents
        -->

          <!-- Example row of columns -->
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <h2 style="color:#5bc0de">Step 1</h2>
              <p class="indent">
                Before joining any group, you need to find your classes first!
                You can add your classes by clicking "Add another class" and the drop down menu
                will appear. As soon as you click one of the classes from the list, it will 
                automatically add that class for you. 
              </p>
              <img src="/images/help1.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-12" id="mypagebody">
              <h2 style="color:#5bc0de">Step 2</h2>
              <p class="indent">
                This is a list of your saved classes on your left. If you click on the subject, it will 
                direct you to the class page. From the class page, you can see the full list
                of groups associated. If you are not in that group, you would not see any relevant 
                information until you join. 
              </p>
              <img src="/images/help2.png" style="padding:10px;">
           </div>
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <h2 style="color:#5bc0de">Step 3</h2>
              <p class="indent">
                After choosing class, we will show the the groups already formed by other Groupers.
                There are two different lists for the group: one type is IN-PERSON and the other
                is ONLINE. If you click a group from IN-PERSON, it will show you information about
                group meetings. If you choose ONLINE instead, it will go to the form pages.
              </p>
              <p class="indent">
                If you do not like groups already formed, you can always create one yourself
                by clicking CREATE GROUP button on the side!
              </p>
              <img src="/images/help3.png" style="padding:10px;">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div> <!-- Finish help contents! -->

      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>